0.name: A Path to the Mansion
desc: "   The path to the mansion is overrun with years of tall weeds and uncut grass.
Westend Lane lies to the west, flourishing with the traffic of a busy city.  To
the east you can see a gigantic mansion lying in the distance.  The mansion
has obviously been neglected as every aspect of the structure looks disheveled
and in disrepair.  It is going to be difficult to make your way to the mansion
with all this thick underbrush.

1.name: A Weed-Covered Yard
desc: "   The tall weeds and uncut grass cover the wide and green yard like a long-
haired blanket.  It is obvious that no one has attended to the maintenance of
this place.  The echo of something barking begins to creep across the lawn.  Is
the sound coming from the mansion or is there something creeping within the
flora?  It appears the only way to know is further exploration across the
unkempt lawn.  A path leading out to Westend Lane can be seen to the west.  The
gigantic mansion lies in the distance to the east in all its broken-down glory.

2.name: A Weed-Covered Yard
desc: "   The tall weeds and uncut grass cover the wide and green yard like a long-
haired blanket.  A strong, steel fence blocks any further travel to the north
and west.  Looking through the fence to the west, you can see the citizens
of Midgard hustle and bustle along Westend Lane.  A gigantic mansion lies at
the end of the lawn in the distance to the east.  The unkempt lawn continues
to the east and south.  It is obvious that no one has attended to the
maintenance of this place.  The echo of something barking floats eerily through
the air across the lawn.  Is the sound coming from the mansion or is there
something creeping within the flora?

3.name: A Weed-Covered Yard
desc: "   The tall weeds and uncut grass cover the wide and green yard like a long-
haired blanket.  A strong, steel fence blocks any further travel to the south
and west.  Looking through the fence to the west, you can see the citizens
of Midgard hustle and bustle along Westend Lane.  A gigantic mansion lies at
the end of the lawnn in the distance to the east.  The unkempt lawn continues

4.name: A Weed-Covered Yard
desc: "   A gigantic mansion towers above you directly to the east.  There is an
old wooden door in the side of the mansion that must grant access within.
The run-down structure is in complete disrepair from years, even decades of
neglect.  The windows all along the side of the mansion are cracked or
broken.  The window shades on the sides of the windows are either hanging
for their lives by a rusty nail or completely missing.  The tall weeds and
uncut grass cover the wide and green yard like a long-haired blanket.
The unkempt lawn continues to the north, west and south.  It is obvious
that no one has attended to the maintenance of this place.  There is a
doormat here that reads, "BEWARE OF DOGS".  The echo of something barking
floats eerily through the air across the lawn.  Is the sound coming from
the mansion or is there something creeping within the flora?  The hustle
and bustle of citizens going about their business can be seen in the
distance along Westend Lane to the west.

5.name: A Weed-Covered Yard
desc: "   A gigantic mansion towers above you directly to the east.  The run-down

6.name: A Weed-Covered Yard

7.name: By the Front Door
desc: "   The barking and howling is coming even louder from the hallway directly
to the east.  The wooden and rotting front door to the mansion is closed to
the west.  The floor of the house is made of faded wooden planks and is
covered in grime and dog hair.  There is an awful stench emanating from within
the gigantic structure that seems to be a mixture of body odor and urine
stains, more than likely human and canine.  It is probably best just to run
back out the door to the west, but curiosity begs you deeper within the filthy
mansion.

8.name: A Hallway through the Mansion
desc: "   The hallway through the mansion continues to the north and south.
There is a rotting wooden door at the end of the hallway to the west that
must allow escape from this awful place.  Who or what could be living in
such squalor?  There is a door to the east the more than like leads to one
of the gigantic mansion's many rooms.  Dirt, filth and dog hair cover the
wooden planks of the mansion's floor.  It is obvious no one has cleaned
this place in years.  Loud and ear-splitting barking bounces off the walls
of the hallway.  It is difficult to ascertain exactly which direction it is
coming from.  The barking seems to be coming from every direction!

9.name: A Small and Filthy Room
desc: "   The room looks smaller than it actually is is due to the extreme clutter
that litters the room.  Someone has shoved boxes and crates of various sizes
all over the room.  There is barely a path to walk from the front of the room
to retrieve any of the items within.  Dust and dog hair cover almost every
item in the room.  The residents of the mansions have probably not been
in this room in years.  The only way out seems to be back through the door
to the west.

10.name: A Hallway through the Mansion
desc: "   The hallway through the mansion continues to the north and south.  There
are closed wooden doors to the east and west of the hallway that more than
likely lead to one the gigantic structure's many rooms.  There is an awful
stench emanating throughout the hallway that seems to be a mixture of body
odor and drying urine, most probably a mixture of human and canine.  Looking
closer at the long wooden planks that line the floor, you can see scattered
dirt, filth and dog hair lying all over the ground.  It is obvious no one
has cleaned this place in years.  Loud and ear-splitting barking bounces off
the walls of the hallway.  It is difficult to ascertain exactly which direction
it is coming from.  The barking seems to be coming from every direction!

12.name: A Dusty and Unkempt Room
desc: "   This room is a horrible mess.  No one has dusted or swept up in what
appears to be years.  The room is full of boxes and crates piled on top of
mass amounts of unused furniture.  Is it that hard to take a second and
clean up this mess?  There is a door along the west wall that leads back
into the hallway of the mansion.  A large dog door to the east of the room
leads to a back yard full of green grass.

13.name: A Hallway through the Mansion
desc: "   The hallway through the mansion continues to the north and south.  There

canine.  Looking closer at the long wooden planks that line the floor, you
can see scattered remnants of dirt, filth and dog hair lying all over the
ground.  It is obvious no one has cleaned this place in years.  Loud and
ear-splitting barking bounces off the walls of the hallway.  It is difficult
to ascertain exactly which direction it is coming from.  The baking seems
to be coming from every direction!

14.name: Blanket's Room
desc: "   This room has been torn to shreds.  The floors are covered in pillows of
every size, shape and color.  However, a good amount of them have been ripped
apart and are bleeding their precious stuffing.  A nest of some kind has
formed in the northeast most section of the room.  It is obvious that this
is the resting and sleeping place of one of the mansion's dogs.  A plaque
nailed to the eastern wall reads, "Blanket".  The only way out appears to be
through the door along the western wall.

15.name: A Well-Stocked Kitchen
desc: "   This is probably the cleanest place in the entire mansion.  Which is sad
to say because this place is still a pigsty.  Food in various stages of
assembly lie across the kitchen counters.  Slabs of different kinds of meat
and ropes of spices hang from the ceiling.  Someone must be trying to keep
these items away from the dogs.  A wretched smell drifts in from the north.
What could be going on in there?

16.name: A Staircare at the End of the Hallway
desc: "   The hallway through the mansion continues to the north.  A broken-down
wooden staircase leads up to the second floor of the house.  There are
closed wooden doors to the east and west of the hallway that more than likely

and drying urine, most probably a mixture of human and canine.  Looking
closer at the long wooden planks that line the floor, you can see scattered

It is obvious no one has cleaned this place in years.  Loud and ear-
splitting barking bounces off the walls of the hallway.  It is difficult to

17.name: The Master Kitchen
desc: "   The kitchen is cluttered with dishes, both dirty and relatively clean.

The smell coming from this place is nauseating.  It almost seems to stick

Looking closely at the floor, you can make out the faint outline of a

28.name: A Dark and Dank Dungeon
desc: "   The bottom of the mansion is completely dark except for a light emitting

in back of the desk.  It swivels back and forth repeatedly as whoever is
sitting in the chair stares blankly into the box.  What could that person
be looking at?  Looking around the room you do not see any other furniture.
What a sad existence to only have a desk, chair and box for the rest of
whoever's pathetic life it is.  The handles attached to the bottom of the
trapdoor lead back up to the office above.
